HEADWORD: Aërobic
<hw>A`⟦eum⟧r*o"bic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Growing or thriving only in the presence of oxygen; also,
pertaining to, or induced by, a⟦eum⟧robies; <as>as, <ex>a⟦eum⟧robic</ex>
fermentation</as>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>A`⟦eum⟧r*o"bic*al*ly</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
